3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method to incorporate temporal dependencies into occupancy models, which is a common problem in machine learning. The use of a rich high-dimensional feature space also supports this category.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a method to predict future occupancy levels, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence. The use of a rich high-dimensional feature space also supports this category.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper addresses the problem of real-time performance of the algorithm, which is a common problem in systems and control. The use of LIDAR data also supports this category.
